description.text:
You are cordially invited to attend the US Investment Expo taking place in Delhi on March 16th from 11am to 8pm. This expo will present information about immigration to America through investment, and will provide exciting options for you and your family. Have all of your investment-based US immigration questions answered. You will get to meet multiple US immigration attorneys who can give you personalized advise on your immigration options. You will get to meet multiple US-based investment programs which can help you and your family get Green Cards fast.
PROGRAM 
US Immigration Attorneys and US investment firms will be available to talk to you throughout the day from 11am to 8pm. There will be short presentations by immigration attorneys and investment firms throughout the day. Complimentary refreshments will be served.
What is an EB-5 Investor Visa?
An EB-5 investor visa a United States visa which provides a method of obtaining a green card for foreign nationals who invest money in the United States. The EB-5 investor visa may allow foreign investors in commercial enterprises that will benefit the economy and create or maintain at least 10 full-time jobs to become eligible for a green card. The EB-5 investor visa is also referred to as the Employment Based Fifth Preference category of visas, hence, "EB-5."
Speakers:
Rohit Turkhud (Master of Ceremonies)  Fakhoury Global Immigration
Rohit Turkhud (Discussion Leader) has been specializing in the practice of the US Immigration & Nationality Laws since 1985. For the first 9 years of his career his practiced focused on asylum and removal cases. Since 1994 he has been specializing in employment based and family based matters. From 1994 to 2001 Rohit served in senior executive positions at IT companies and headed their legal and international recruiting divisions. He was an integral part of setting up an IT company's UK operations and travelled extensively to the UK in the discharge of those responsibilities. From June 2004 to September 2012 he was a partner at the Law Offices of Cyrus S. Nallaseth PLLC, and at Nallaseth & Turkhud PLLC. He continues to focus on employment based immigration matters. Rohit has joined FLG, as a partner, in the pursuit of excellence and expansion. Rohit seeks to contribute to the international growth of FLG and help ensure that we always provide the quality of services and attention to customer satisfaction that has catapulted FLG to the top of law firms specializing in the field of immigration laws. He is proud to be a member of a team that reaches from Miami to San Francisco and from New York to Denver, with Michigan being the heart of the network. He has authored a frequent immigration law column for India Today's North American edition. He is a guest speaker on business immigration issues, specially relating to H-1B and the new PERM rules and regulations. He has authored an article in the second edition of the authoritative "THE PERM BOOK". On the second and fourth Tuesday of each month, Rohit hosts a prime time LIVE immigration show on Jus Punjabi, a national cable network channel. Mr. Turkhud is fluent in the Hindi, Gujarati and Marathi languages.
Mark Davies   Davies &Associates, LLC Immigration Attorneys
Dual qualified as a lawyer in the United States and the United Kingdom, Mark I. Davies is the Global Managing Partner and founder of our firm. Mark also Chairs our Global Business and Investor visa team and focuses his practice on EB5, L1, E2 and other business and investor visa solutions. A former General Counsel, Mark is relied on as primary counsel to major corporations, investors, non-profits and businesses of all sizes.
Mark holds a Juris Doctorate degree from the University of Pennsylvania Law School, a law degree from a major university in the United Kingdom (UK) and an MBA degree from the University of Pennsylvania's Wharton School of Business. Mark was awarded a post-graduate Fellowship from the University of Pennsylvania law school and is the holder of multiple scholarships and academic awards.
Mark has also published legal articles and spoken on an international basis. His speaking engagements include presentations for various US state bar associations, the Association of Corporate Counsel, the Law Society of England & Wales and the ALA.
Mark has been recognized by the White House for his service within the US legal profession.
Matt Gordon  E3IG
Mr. Gordon’s career spans business operations, finance and law. Mr. Gordon is a noted expert in the EB-5 field and is an authority on structuring EB-5 investments. He is the editor of the EB-5 Book, the legal treatise on the EB-5 program and a frequent lecturer to immigration attorneys. Mr. Gordon has participated in policy events, including those hosted by the White House and Harvard University’s Kennedy School of Government.Prior to found E3 Investment Group, Mr. Gordon was an investment banker for a decade and ran the US division of a Swiss multi-national corporation. Mr. Gordon is a licensed attorney, having practiced mergers and acquisitions law at the beginning of his career with the largest and most reputable Wall Street firms including Fried Frank and Sullivan & Cromwell.Mr. Gordon received his B.S. in Policy Analysis from Cornell University and his J.D., cum laude, from the University of Pennsylvania School of Law. Mr. Gordon holds FINRA/SEC securities licenses and is associated with a registered broker-dealer.
Randal L. Berry American United Group
Dr. Berry is the Director of Business Development, responsible for project development and marketing of projects suitably structured to satisfy EB5 designation under the USCIS’s guidelines of partnership and investment. Dr. Berry brings with him over 25 years of diversified international business and education management experience, serving throughout the United States, Canada and China. His specialization has been in the fields of International Management Strategy in private sector business and private / public education in positions of management, administration and consulting,
Prior to joining AURC, Dr. Berry was the Senior Business and Finance Strategist with WSIC, Ltd., China and SIS, Inc., US, International Business Investment Consulting Groups in Guangzhou, PRC and San Francisco, US and an Adjunct Professor of International Management at Southern New Hampshire University, Manchester, NH.
During his career, Dr. Berry has worked in the fields of Strategic Business and Finance Management, Education Management, Investment Strategy and Management, Finance and Business Strategy Consulting, EB5 Program Project Consulting, Management and Development, and Construction Management in the US, China and Canada. 
Dr. Berry holds an MBA from NYIT in Manhattan, NY, and a DBA from Walden University, MN in the areas of Global and International Business Management and Administration.  
Niraj (Nick) Sheth  CEO of LD Capital LLC
Niraj Sheth is President & CEO of LD Capital LLC - providing commercial real estate loans from $3 million-$200 million, small business financing for deals ranging from $100,000 to $6 million, and loans for FF&E.

Peter Bibler  the Related’s Investment 
Department for Asia based in Shanghai, China. He is an American attorney experienced in real estate & consumer law. Since 2010, Peter has lived in Shanghai, China. Prior to joining Related, Peter also worked in the legal department of a large Chinese real estate developer, supporting its investment activities.
Avinash Nichkawde  
Avinash Nichkawde (Emcee) is an Entrepreneur, Chartered Accountant, and International Business Consultant with special interest in the area of EB-5 Investment based Migration to USA. He started his tax practice in Sydney, Australia in ‘93 and grew to 7000 clients in 4 years, he later went into International Education Business and at peak managed over 200 employees besides consulting numerous small to medium companies over the years. He brings vast practical global experience to clients. Born & Raised in India, Avinash is a Australian citizen having lived there for over 20 years and now residing permanently in USA, with travels to over 30 countries. He is known for providing out of the box practical solutions for his clients which are very cost effective. Avinash is Advisor to Second Street Capital and iMedGo,Inc which are based in San Jose California.  He has a lively personality with special interest in meditation, music, poetry and philosophy. 
Gonzalo Lopez Jordan American Regional Center Group 
Mr. Lopez-Jordan is a manager and co-founding partner of American Regional Center Group (“ARCG”) and is also CEO and founding partner of Patagonia Financial Holdings, a value oriented Private Equity Firm.  After extensively researching the EB-5 industry on behalf of several clients, Mr. Lopez Jordan oversaw Patagonia’s entrance to the EB-5 market with the aim of using his firm’s significant financial structuring and investment experience to fill inefficiencies he found in the marketplace.  Its first Regional Center, Geothermal Regional Center LLC received its USCIS designation on September 8, 2011. After the successful launch of GRP, Mr. Lopez Jordan formed ARCG as a platform to build a larger portfolio of EB-5 Regional Centers.  American Regional Center Group currently manages seven Regional Centers.
Mr. Lopez Jordan has twenty years of senior management experience in asset management, private banking, securities trading and alternative Investments. Prior to founding Patagonia Financial Holdings, Mr. Lopez-Jordan was First Vice President- Senior Investment Management Specialist at Smith Barney Inc. From 1995 to 1999, Mr. Lopez- Jordan was a Vice President for the private bank at Banco Santander International Miami, where he provided financial planning assistance and portfolio optimization for clients in multiple jurisdictions. Mr. Lopez-Jordan holds a Juris Doctorate (J.D.) from Facolta di Giurisprudenza Universita di Pisa-Italy and another J.D. from Facultad de Derecho de Oviedo-Spain and M.B.A. from Instituto Universitario de la Empresa Universidad de Oviedo-Spain.
(Many more speakers will be added and annouced day by day)

What is an EB-5 Investor Visa?

An EB-5 investor visa a United States visa which provides a method of obtaining a green card for foreign nationals who invest money in the United States. The EB-5 investor visa may allow foreign investors in commercial enterprises that will benefit the economy and create or maintain at least 10 full-time jobs to become eligible for a green card. Are you game for some crazy fun and lot of masti !!

While most of the state is commercialised, West Sikkim has still kept its rich culture and heritage alive. Sikkim is one of the prominent destination for travel enthusiasts because of Himalayas, gorging waterfalls, snowcapped mountains, monasteries, flora and fauna. Not to forget the authentic momos and sumptuous thupka.

Darjeeling on the other hand is surrounded by emerald-green tea plantations and towered over by the majestic Khangchendzonga (8598m).

Itinerary:

Day 1: Namchi

Pick up from Bagdogra airport or New Jalpaiguri railway station and reach Namchi via taxi. Enter the most beautiful state of India – ‘Sikkim’. You get to spend the evening to yourself.





Day 2: Namchi-Pelling

Visit Tendong Hill and Char Dham in Namchi and in the Afternoon, take the mesmerising route to Pelling, appreciating the beauty of this natural wonder





Day 3: Pelling

This day we visit the beautiful Kanchenjunga Falls, Khecheopalri Lake and Pemayangtse Monastery. A quiet and serene pathway takes you through sometimes steep and winding roads of the hills.







Day 4: Pelling

Trek for around 3 kms in morning to see one of the most beautiful Monastery and some mesmerising views on the way. This is a special day as today we will spend some memorable time in an NGO with some adorable kids. And later walk upto Rabdanse Ruins to enjoy the spectacular views of the Kanchendzong hill ranges.









Day 5: Pelling-Darjeeling

After breakfast, we will leave for Darjeeling- ‘The Queen of Hills’. On the way we will see Tea farms and visit a Japanese temple. We spend the evening relaxing and everyone is encouraged to explore the locality.



Day 6: Darjeeling

Visit Tiger Hill early morning situated at an altitude of 8000 feet for an amazing view of Mount Kanchenjunga and then some sight seeing of Darjeeling including Himalayan Mountaineering Institute and Darjeeling Zoo. In the evening we’ll enjoy a farewell group dinner and one last night out together before we part ways at the end of this most memorable trip.





Day 7: Darjeeling-Bagdogra Airport/ New Jalpaiguri Railway Station

Time to bid adieu. Check out from hotel and transfer to Bagdogra airport or New Jalpaiguri Railway Station via taxi for your onward journey.

End of this memorable tour.

We amalgamate and unite the Indian healthcare travel sector to create an effective and sustainable medical tourism model with MORAL and ETHICAL values. At MTDA we understand the importance of both traditional and regular medical procedures. We strive hard to strike a balance between the two and promote both procedures. For this we have plan to tie up with various government bodies, which are promoting Indian systems of medication such as AYUSH - Ayurveda, Yoga, Unani, Siddha and Homeopathy.
Please visit MTDA website; www.mtda.org.in

Medical Tourism Development Alliance proudly presents its 1st edition of the Medical Tourism Excellence Awards (MTEA) 2017 on Saturday, April 15, 2017 at New Delhi. The awards ceremony is held in keeping with MTDA’s commitment to recognize the tremendous efforts of government bodies, doctors, hospitals, healthcare facilitators and medical interpreters that maintained consistently high standard of patient care deliveries with quality and demonstrated outstanding performance in their reputed domain. The award categories cover healthcare and healthcare travel segments.
The award ceremony also provides an exceptional opportunity for your organization to interact with key industry leaders through an engaging and informative program featuring renowned speakers and dynamic sessions. Prominent industry experts will highlight the latest development and transformation of healthcare and healthcare travel industry. MTEA 2017 is open to healthcare & medical tourism professionals from around the globe. It is a platform to bring together the various stakeholders in the healthcare and medical tourism for exchange of ideas and best practices. MTEA 2017 is a WORLD RENOWNED MARK OF EXCELLENCE.

MTEA 2017 honors the healthcare and medical tourism fraternity for their dedication and hard work to transform patients care and outcomes. The awards are open to hospitals, clinics, healthcare facilitators, medical tourism companies and medical interpreters. Award winners are invited to attend a glittering awards ceremony and have right to use the prestigious LOGO in their marketing. All organization may submit single or multiple entries but not more than 5.
